  "texts": [
    "(2) The distribution of evaluation dataset licenses shows a preference for widely recognized licenses such as, Apache-2.0 and MIT.",
    "The overall pattern of distribution in these protocols underscores the delicate equilibrium sought within the LLMs data evaluation domain, balancing knowledge sharing and intellectual property protection.",
    "The flexibility provided by open licenses such as Apache-2.0 and MIT contributes to the widespread use and sharing of evaluation datasets, which is essential for advancing relative research.",
    "(3) The majority of evaluation datasets fall within the 0-100K size range, with datasets containing fewer than 10K samples constituting 56.4% of the total.",
    "This indicates that many tasks can be effectively assessed with relatively small datasets, which may be also due to cost considerations during dataset construction and evaluation."
